Developing and enhancing the students main instrument skills in practical lessons and independent practice. The student will delve into traditional folk musicians' repertoire, playing styles and techiques, mastering traditional repertoire as well as composed and improvisational musical material.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims at guiding the student in improving his instrumental/singing skills. Students will become acquainted with playing styles of traditional musicians (archive recordings, live performances) and get familiar with their repertoire. Students will develop their own individual playing style, using creatively elements of traditional music (incl improvisation). Acquired knowledge is applyed as a soloist and as an ensemble member.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completing the course, the student will - aquire advanced theoretical knowledge and skills for analyzing traditional folk music repertoire and apply this experience in practice; - demonstrate advanced level of technical and stylistic capacity for realizing musical ideas on a high level of proficieny; - demonstrate knowledge of rythmical nyances of traditional functional dance music; - demonstrate skills and knowledge for using various information sources on traditional music.
